243
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:43,280
Blind guides.

244
00:41:44,880 --> 00:41:49,640
You are stray and inept,
and swallow camel.

245
00:41:50,600 --> 00:41:55,880
You bow before the letter of the law,
and violate the heart of the law

246
00:41:56,280 --> 00:42:00,880
justice! Mercy! Good faith.

247
00:42:02,040 --> 00:42:06,880
You are like white washed tombs,
all fair and clean without,

248
00:42:06,960 --> 00:42:11,760
but within full of death
and bones and all corruption.

249
00:42:12,560 --> 00:42:14,960
You see these stones, do you not?

250
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:23,760
I tell you there will not be left here one
stone upon another that will not be throne down.

251
00:42:23,920 --> 00:42:28,280
Yours is a house of damnation,

252
00:42:28,600 --> 00:42:31,600
the home of the ligard and spider.

253
00:42:33,440 --> 00:42:37,320
Serpents through their vipers.

254
00:42:37,520 --> 00:42:41,040
How can any of you escape damnation?

255
00:42:46,720 --> 00:42:51,720
You shall not see me here again,
not until you learn to cry,

256
00:42:51,760 --> 00:42:55,440
"Blessed is he who comes
in the name of the Lord,

257
00:42:55,920 --> 00:43:00,200
for I and my Father are one
and the same."

258
00:43:00,240 --> 00:43:02,480
He is a blasphemer!

259
00:43:02,560 --> 00:43:04,200
This is the man!

260
00:43:10,800 --> 00:43:13,520
You don't speak for
the people of Israel!

261
00:43:13,520 --> 00:43:15,800
Listen to the teachings of our God!

262
00:43:23,120 --> 00:43:25,000
He should be stoned to death!

263
00:43:25,200 --> 00:43:27,240
He's a blasphemer!

264
00:43:29,880 --> 00:43:31,280
Wonder what's going on?

265
00:43:32,240 --> 00:43:34,000
I don't like it, I'll take a look.

266
00:43:34,560 --> 00:43:36,680
- Look after, stand, will you?
- All right

267
00:43:38,520 --> 00:43:42,800
Caspar!

268
00:43:46,360 --> 00:43:48,320
A righteous man. A righteous man.

269
00:43:55,960 --> 00:43:57,160
Kill the Romans!

270
00:44:02,800 --> 00:44:04,080
Come on!

271
00:44:04,880 --> 00:44:07,760
He's not the messiah!
He's a false prophet.

272
00:44:08,400 --> 00:44:10,040
He a friend of the Romans!

273
00:44:10,160 --> 00:44:13,080
Stone him! Stone him! Stone him!

274
00:44:14,320 --> 00:44:16,360
Traitor! Traitor to Israel!

275
00:44:16,880 --> 00:44:20,280
Traitor! Traitor! Traitor!

276
00:44:27,400 --> 00:44:28,480
He speaks the truth!

277
00:44:32,680 --> 00:44:38,240
Stone him to death!
Stone him to death!

278
00:44:57,280 --> 00:44:58,320
Peter!

279
00:45:11,840 --> 00:45:14,400
If you please,
I've come to offer my help.

280
00:45:14,480 --> 00:45:15,560
Master Nicodemus.

281
00:45:15,640 --> 00:45:19,440
Yes, I must advise you.
You are in danger.

282
00:45:19,440 --> 00:45:21,920
Please persuade your master to
keep away from public places.

283
00:45:22,000 --> 00:45:25,080
God must have sent you,
master Nicodemus. You speak to him.

284
00:45:25,160 --> 00:45:28,160
Of all people,
he will listen to you. Come.

285
00:45:32,800 --> 00:45:34,080
Master!

286
00:45:52,120 --> 00:45:53,200
Rabbi.

287
00:45:56,040 --> 00:45:59,040
There is to be a meeting
at the Sanhedrin.

288
00:46:00,000 --> 00:46:01,720
You have many enemies there,

289
00:46:01,800 --> 00:46:06,720
but also friends who know that
you are a teacher come from God,

290
00:46:06,760 --> 00:46:12,920
for no man that shows the signs
or has the words that you impart,

291
00:46:12,960 --> 00:46:14,960
unless God giveth them.

292
00:46:16,080 --> 00:46:23,680
And yet, my heart is troubled,
and my mind confused.

293
00:46:24,400 --> 00:46:28,320
You must help me to see the truth.

294
00:46:28,400 --> 00:46:32,000
Accept the man to be born again,
Nicodemus.

295
00:46:34,240 --> 00:46:36,800
He cannot see the kingdom of God.

296
00:46:37,280 --> 00:46:38,680
Born again?

297
00:46:40,160 --> 00:46:43,800
Can a man enter his mother's
womb the second time?

298
00:46:45,760 --> 00:46:48,680
That which is born of the
flesh is flesh.

299
00:46:50,320 --> 00:46:53,360
That which is born of
the spirit is spirit.

300
00:47:00,480 --> 00:47:03,680
Do not marvel that I said to you,
"You must be born again."

301
00:47:06,960 --> 00:47:14,320
The wind blows where it will,
and you hear the sound of it,

302
00:47:16,800 --> 00:47:19,880
but you don't know whence
it comes or whether it goes.

303
00:47:20,600 --> 00:47:23,520
And so it is with everyone
who is born with the spirit.

304
00:47:27,080 --> 00:47:31,080
God so loved the world that
he sent his own son,

305
00:47:31,080 --> 00:47:36,000
that whosoever believed in him
should not perish, but have eternal life.

306
00:47:39,760 --> 00:47:43,480
God sent his son to the world
not to condemn it,

307
00:47:45,440 --> 00:47:48,320
but that the world should
be saved through him.

308
00:47:53,040 --> 00:47:58,680
He came to Jerusalem. The crowd
went wild for his arrival and we did nothing!

309
00:47:59,120 --> 00:48:05,960
He then scolded the merchants, so they
sent us beasts for sacrifice from the courtyard
to the temple and we did not intervene!

310
00:48:06,000 --> 00:48:11,760
How many times have we protested that the disgrace
of buy traders being allowed in the precincts of the temple?

311
00:48:11,960 --> 00:48:16,520
But then we allowed him to preach
in the holy temple itself, and at no time,

312
00:48:17,000 --> 00:48:20,240
no time did he recognize
your authority, Caiaphus,

313
00:48:20,680 --> 00:48:22,600
nor made sufficient
to the elders of Israel.

314
00:48:24,560 --> 00:48:26,640
We must denounce him
in the name of the people of Israel!

315
00:48:28,840 --> 00:48:33,120
I'm not sure.
I'm not sure that we have that right.

316
00:48:34,440 --> 00:48:39,400
Can we honestly say that we represent the
true thoughts and aspirations of the people of Israel?

317
00:48:39,520 --> 00:48:40,280
What are you saying?

318
00:48:40,360 --> 00:48:46,120
I've often wondered if we, as elders are
too cut off from them and their real problems.

319
00:48:46,160 --> 00:48:48,880
How can we guide them if we do not
know what's in their hearts?

320
00:48:48,920 --> 00:48:52,200
But without our guidance
they would be lost!

321
00:48:52,280 --> 00:48:55,800
People, people will run after
any new thing.

322
00:48:55,880 --> 00:48:59,280
They have taken up with this man,
with his hijinx and his exaggerated promises.

323
00:48:59,360 --> 00:49:02,960
I have seen him,
I have seen him preach.

324
00:49:03,120 --> 00:49:07,120
His words reach into men's hearts,
not like ours.

325
00:49:07,120 --> 00:49:14,440
It's not through the old rituals, the old formulas,
but a new vision which seems to answer all their hopes.

326
00:49:14,520 --> 00:49:20,760
A message of comfort, of goodness, of purity,
of the virtues of humility.

327
00:49:20,840 --> 00:49:24,240
We've heard it all before, from the John
the Baptist and hundreds of others.

328
00:49:29,320 --> 00:49:31,520
Yes, how's those who follow
to hate him as the Messiah?

329
00:49:31,560 --> 00:49:34,360
He's a blasphemer! He's an imposter!

330
00:49:36,880 --> 00:49:41,960
With respect to those more learned
than I, there is one possibility

331
00:49:41,960 --> 00:49:46,320
that it seems no one
here is ready to consider...

332
00:49:46,400 --> 00:49:47,640
What is it?

333
00:49:48,040 --> 00:49:52,280
The possibility that
Jesus of Nazareth

334
00:49:52,560 --> 00:49:57,480
may be in fact be the messiah
awaited by our people.

335
00:49:57,800 --> 00:50:01,560
A carpenter from Galilee?

336
00:50:01,560 --> 00:50:09,280
suddenly, he never misses a chance
to identify himself with them.

337
00:50:09,440 --> 00:50:10,280
Exactly!

338
00:50:10,360 --> 00:50:17,080
I only know that like our brother
Joseph, I've heard him preach.

339
00:50:17,840 --> 00:50:22,160
I was moved lifted out of my soul,

340
00:50:23,080 --> 00:50:28,320
and seemed to see all things
in a new and blinding light.

341
00:50:28,640 --> 00:50:37,360
I was aware of wonders, signs
that God may be with him,

342
00:50:38,120 --> 00:50:41,920
and through him, with us.

343
00:50:44,200 --> 00:50:47,800
Do you realize what you are
saying, Master Nicodemus?

344
00:50:47,880 --> 00:50:50,160
Let him speak!

345
00:50:50,400 --> 00:50:53,320
Listen to him! Let him speak!
Don't shut him down!

346
00:50:53,360 --> 00:50:56,400
The coming of the messiah
is the heart of our faith.

347
00:50:56,400 --> 00:50:58,720
Why should he not come now?

348
00:50:58,760 --> 00:51:04,200
Why do we dream our liberator will be
revealed in glory, a new Solomon, a new David?

349
00:51:04,800 --> 00:51:07,400
Is God not allowed to choose
who he wishes?

350
00:51:07,400 --> 00:51:10,280
Even the son of a poor carpenter
from Nazareth?

351
00:51:10,280 --> 00:51:13,440
David began life as a shepherd.

352
00:51:13,480 --> 00:51:17,360
Who are we to decide the way in which
God should choose to help his people?

353
00:51:17,600 --> 00:51:23,720
We are grains of sand,
chalk blown in the wind.

354
00:51:23,720 --> 00:51:27,240
May the Lord open our
eyes to his wisdom.

355
00:51:29,700 --> 00:51:34,580
Master Nicodemus,
I have always respected you.

356
00:51:35,660 --> 00:51:39,420
How am I to understand your
defense of this man,

357
00:51:40,180 --> 00:51:43,260
whose missions seems to be
to divide our people?

358
00:51:43,340 --> 00:51:49,740
Even this noble assembly
has been torn asunder by him.

359
00:51:51,060 --> 00:51:56,740
This Jesus of Nazareth must be
an extraordinary man.

360
00:51:57,020 --> 00:52:04,060
But is there not one among you who
understands the the real significance of this matter.

361
00:52:04,060 --> 00:52:09,780
It is not the Galilean's words that are important.
The so called miracles,

362
00:52:10,380 --> 00:52:15,780
even the fact the frenzied crowds hail
him as the messiah, it's not important.

363
00:52:17,060 --> 00:52:26,740
The central core of this case is
that this man dares to proclaim...

364
00:52:27,220 --> 00:52:31,100
I can hardly make myself say it.

365
00:52:32,300 --> 00:52:37,660
This man dares to proclaim himself

366
00:52:38,980 --> 00:52:43,020
the, the son of God.

367
00:52:48,620 --> 00:52:52,860
This man, while claiming to
uphold the law,

368
00:52:53,700 --> 00:52:59,060
perverts our most fundamental beliefs.

369
00:53:02,940 --> 00:53:12,620
Our losses, the prophets who claims
to say in the name of God things

370
00:53:12,660 --> 00:53:19,100
which God has not commanded,
that prophet must die.

371
00:53:22,660 --> 00:53:27,220
if this man Jesus is a false prophet
and a blasphemer,

372
00:53:28,060 --> 00:53:33,700
is it not better for one man to die,
than a for a whole nation to perish?

373
00:53:35,900 --> 00:53:39,580
However, under Roman occupation,
Caiaphus,

374
00:53:39,580 --> 00:53:44,540
the people of Israel may put a goat to
death, but not a man.

375
00:53:44,540 --> 00:53:49,460
Thank you, Zerah for reminding
us of our realities.

376
00:53:51,220 --> 00:53:57,180
Then he must be charged and
found guilty by the Romans.

377
00:53:57,260 --> 00:53:59,700
But Caiaphus,
we have not found him guilty yet!

378
00:53:59,700 --> 00:54:05,420
Surely our law does not condemn a man before
first giving him hearing before the elders of Israel?

379
00:54:05,500 --> 00:54:10,900
No matter how serious his offense, we cannot
simply hand over one of our brothers to the Romans.

380
00:54:10,940 --> 00:54:16,820
Caiaphus, after the Passover let me
persuade Jesus to come to us and explain to us

381
00:54:16,900 --> 00:54:21,260
what is in his heart and his mind
when he says he is the son of God.

382
00:54:21,360 --> 00:54:22,360
No!

383
00:54:23,400 --> 00:54:27,000
Caiaphus to delay would be
too dangerous.

384
00:54:27,120 --> 00:54:31,040
We all know what steps Pilate would
take against our people if the unrest continues.

385
00:54:31,520 --> 00:54:34,400
Zerah, he must beaken tonight.

386
00:54:34,400 --> 00:54:39,320
It could cause even more trouble among the
crowds if our temple guards go searching for him.

387
00:54:41,580 --> 00:54:44,700
I think I know the way to reach him.

388
00:54:47,060 --> 00:54:54,020
Zerah, don't forget Jesus of Nazareth
is one of our brothers.

389
00:55:05,021 --> 00:55:05,976
Judas?

390
00:55:06,101 --> 00:55:10,777
I've not been able to find you. You weren't
seen with the Master for the Iast few days.

391
00:55:10,901 --> 00:55:12,857
Where have you been?

392
00:55:15,421 --> 00:55:17,377
I've been trying to think.

393
00:55:22,581 --> 00:55:24,537
Trying to decide what to do.

394
00:55:24,661 --> 00:55:26,891
You seemed to be very sure of what to do.

395
00:55:27,021 --> 00:55:28,977
Oh, I was.

396
00:55:31,781 --> 00:55:33,737
But not now.

397
00:55:35,181 --> 00:55:37,137
I'm confused.

398
00:55:39,101 --> 00:55:42,059
l always believed action - political action -

399
00:55:42,941 --> 00:55:44,897
..would solve everything.

400
00:55:45,021 --> 00:55:50,220
l thought it was enough
to think clearly and act clearly, but...

401
00:55:53,341 --> 00:55:55,297
But I fear my...

402
00:55:55,661 --> 00:55:57,617
..Master does not agree with me.

403
00:56:00,381 --> 00:56:04,613
He doesn't need my ideas.
He says the heart is more important.

404
00:56:07,461 --> 00:56:09,417
Perhaps he's right.

405
00:56:10,621 --> 00:56:12,577
Have I hardened my heart?

406
00:56:13,581 --> 00:56:16,141
Am l fit to be one of his disciples?

407
00:56:19,501 --> 00:56:20,456
I...

408
00:56:23,981 --> 00:56:25,937
l should go home.

409
00:56:28,341 --> 00:56:30,297
Judas, don't lie to yourself.

410
00:56:33,701 --> 00:56:35,817
The truth is that, in your heart,...

411
00:56:36,741 --> 00:56:40,097
..you no longer believe
that Jesus of Nazareth...

412
00:56:40,221 --> 00:56:42,291
..is the Messiah.

413
00:57:01,261 --> 00:57:04,094
There's only one way to know the truth.

414
00:57:04,221 --> 00:57:07,611
You knew that the very first time
that you came to see me.

415
00:57:08,901 --> 00:57:12,211
Let Jesus prove himself...

416
00:57:13,061 --> 00:57:15,017
..before the Sanhedrin.

417
00:57:15,981 --> 00:57:17,937
lt's too late.

418
00:57:20,141 --> 00:57:22,097
He won't accept it.

419
00:57:26,901 --> 00:57:28,300
Why?

420
00:57:28,421 --> 00:57:33,017
There are many influential members
of the council who admire Jesus.

421
00:57:33,141 --> 00:57:35,291
He would be fairly judged.

422
00:57:36,421 --> 00:57:39,219
lf he is the Messiah,
God will not abandon him.

423
00:57:41,141 --> 00:57:43,097
If he is not,...

424
00:57:43,741 --> 00:57:48,132
..then you will have helped to save lsrael
from yet another false prophet.

425
00:58:42,781 --> 00:58:46,217
~ Alleluia!

426
00:58:52,661 --> 00:58:55,221
We are happy to eat
this Passover with you.

427
00:58:57,341 --> 00:59:00,413
l have longed with all my heart
to share it with you.

428
00:59:09,901 --> 00:59:12,973
lt was for this Passover
that l came into the world.

429
00:59:29,261 --> 00:59:31,821
I shall not be with you much longer.

430
00:59:31,941 --> 00:59:33,897
What?!

431
00:59:35,341 --> 00:59:37,332
You will look for me, but...

432
00:59:37,461 --> 00:59:39,497
..where I am going you cannot come.

433
00:59:44,221 --> 00:59:46,781
Master, l will follow you wherever you go.

434
00:59:48,061 --> 00:59:50,017
l will lay down my life for you.

435
00:59:51,781 --> 00:59:53,339
Peter,...

436
00:59:55,341 --> 00:59:58,219
..this very night
before the cock crows twice...

437
00:59:59,781 --> 01:00:03,012
..you will have denied three times
that you even know me.

438
01:00:03,141 --> 01:00:04,972
Oh, my Lord! Never!

439
01:00:14,901 --> 01:00:16,459
Never!

440
01:00:17,701 --> 01:00:19,657
l will never deny you.

441
01:00:22,981 --> 01:00:24,937
You will all lose faith.

442
01:00:28,221 --> 01:00:31,896
The shepherd shall be struck
and the sheep will be scattered.

443
01:00:31,981 --> 01:00:35,735
- l will not lose faith!
- Peter... Peter...

444
01:00:38,381 --> 01:00:40,337
I have prayed for you,...

445
01:00:42,581 --> 01:00:45,220
..and, once you have recovered,...

446
01:00:45,341 --> 01:00:48,890
..you in your turn
must give strength to your brothers.

447
01:01:04,541 --> 01:01:06,497
Truly l tell you...

448
01:01:08,541 --> 01:01:10,497
..one of you is about to betray me.

449
01:01:38,581 --> 01:01:40,537
Master,...

450
01:01:42,101 --> 01:01:44,057
..I'm sick at heart.

451
01:01:45,261 --> 01:01:47,217
Who will betray you?

452
01:01:48,061 --> 01:01:50,017
Is it I?

453
01:01:53,781 --> 01:01:56,853
He who dips his bread in the dish
when I dip mine,...

454
01:01:59,501 --> 01:02:01,457
..he shall be the one.

455
01:02:30,901 --> 01:02:33,131
What you are going to do,...

456
01:02:33,261 --> 01:02:35,217
..do it quickly.

457
01:03:03,261 --> 01:03:05,217
Where's he going?

458
01:03:07,261 --> 01:03:09,217
I don't know.

459
01:03:36,021 --> 01:03:37,977
Blessed be thou, O Lord our God,...

460
01:03:41,901 --> 01:03:44,096
..who has blessed us with thy Laws,...

461
01:03:45,861 --> 01:03:48,421
..and made bread issue from the earth.

462
01:03:50,021 --> 01:03:51,977
From now on...

463
01:03:58,301 --> 01:04:03,295
..this will not be the bread of the passage
of our fathers from bondage to freedom.

464
01:04:05,061 --> 01:04:07,017
This Passover...

465
01:04:08,661 --> 01:04:10,617
..is for you today...

466
01:04:13,261 --> 01:04:15,900
..the passage from the bondage of death...

467
01:04:19,781 --> 01:04:23,330
..to the freedom of life.

468
01:04:36,261 --> 01:04:38,217
This is the bread of life.

469
01:04:46,861 --> 01:04:48,817
Whoever eats of this bread...

470
01:04:49,141 --> 01:04:51,097
..shall have eternal life.

471
01:05:16,461 --> 01:05:18,019
Eat it,...

472
01:05:20,821 --> 01:05:22,379
..for this...

473
01:05:23,221 --> 01:05:25,177
..is my body.

474
01:05:27,861 --> 01:05:30,056
Do this in remembrance of me.

475
01:06:01,581 --> 01:06:03,537
From now on...

476
01:06:03,661 --> 01:06:07,290
..this cup will not only be
a memorial and sacrament...

477
01:06:07,421 --> 01:06:11,016
..of the covenant God made
with our fathers on Mount Sinai.

478
01:06:16,901 --> 01:06:18,857
This is my blood,...

479
01:06:19,901 --> 01:06:23,974
..the blood of the new covenant,
which is to be poured out for many.

480
01:06:31,501 --> 01:06:34,573
l shall not drink again
of the fruit of the vine...

481
01:06:38,581 --> 01:06:40,856
..until the day l drink it with you...

482
01:06:44,621 --> 01:06:46,976
..in my Father's kingdom.

483
01:07:12,341 --> 01:07:14,730
And now I give you
a new commandment,...

484
01:07:17,141 --> 01:07:20,019
..that you love one another
as l have loved you.

485
01:07:24,101 --> 01:07:26,217
Greater love hath no man than this,...

486
01:07:29,021 --> 01:07:32,172
..that a man lay down his life for a friend.

487
01:07:37,421 --> 01:07:39,377
And if you love one another...

488
01:07:42,581 --> 01:07:45,459
..all men shall know that
you are my disciples.

489
01:07:55,701 --> 01:07:57,657
Father,...

490
01:08:00,261 --> 01:08:02,217
..the hour has come.

491
01:08:04,541 --> 01:08:07,339
Glorify thy Son
that thy Son may glorify thee.

492
01:08:11,141 --> 01:08:13,609
Keep in thy name
those thou hast given me.

493
01:08:17,461 --> 01:08:19,417
l do not pray for these only...

494
01:08:21,861 --> 01:08:23,817
..but also for those...

495
01:08:25,221 --> 01:08:27,781
..who believe in me through their word.

496
01:08:44,141 --> 01:08:45,699
I am the way,...

497
01:08:49,141 --> 01:08:50,699
..the truth,...

498
01:08:53,981 --> 01:08:55,539
..and the life.

499
01:09:36,901 --> 01:09:38,857
Peter!

500
01:09:44,261 --> 01:09:45,819
Father,...

501
01:09:46,501 --> 01:09:48,457
..if it is possible,...

502
01:09:49,621 --> 01:09:51,577
..let this cup pass from me.

503
01:10:06,061 --> 01:10:08,017
Let it be...

504
01:10:09,741 --> 01:10:11,697
..as you,...

505
01:10:12,621 --> 01:10:14,577
..not l, would have it.

506
01:10:17,461 --> 01:10:19,417
(distant howling)

507
01:10:23,461 --> 01:10:25,417
(barking)

508
01:11:39,621 --> 01:11:41,577
This is your hour, Judas.

509
01:11:44,701 --> 01:11:46,976
The hour of shadows.

510
01:11:51,021 --> 01:11:52,977
Oh, Master.

511
01:12:04,021 --> 01:12:05,977
You betray your master...

512
01:12:06,981 --> 01:12:08,937
..with a kiss.

513
01:12:19,581 --> 01:12:21,537
That is the man. Arrest him.

514
01:12:23,941 --> 01:12:26,136
Quiet. Don't make any noise.

515
01:12:27,941 --> 01:12:30,330
You go that way.

516
01:12:30,461 --> 01:12:32,417
Try not to wake them.

517
01:12:34,021 --> 01:12:35,215
Judas!

518
01:12:36,021 --> 01:12:37,852
What's happening?

519
01:12:37,981 --> 01:12:40,256
You traitor!

520
01:12:40,381 --> 01:12:42,497
You betrayed him!

521
01:12:42,621 --> 01:12:48,139
Peter, the only way the Master can save
himself is by speaking to the Sanhedrin!

522
01:12:48,261 --> 01:12:51,492
Leave him alone! Let him go!

523
01:12:51,621 --> 01:12:53,213
They'll kill him!

524
01:12:53,341 --> 01:12:54,899
Jesus!

525
01:12:55,021 --> 01:12:56,090
Andrew!

526
01:12:56,221 --> 01:12:57,620
John!

527
01:12:57,741 --> 01:12:59,777
Jesus!

528
01:12:59,901 --> 01:13:01,254
No, Peter!

529
01:13:03,261 --> 01:13:04,933
Get away, scum!

530
01:13:05,061 --> 01:13:06,892
- Arrest them all!
- Zerah!

531
01:13:07,021 --> 01:13:08,977
It was me you sought.

532
01:13:09,901 --> 01:13:12,461
You have found me. Let them go.

533
01:13:15,021 --> 01:13:16,977
Take him away!

534
01:13:17,621 --> 01:13:19,816
Take him to the Sanhedrin!

535
01:13:19,941 --> 01:13:21,897
We must do something!

536
01:13:25,261 --> 01:13:26,819
No!

537
01:13:27,621 --> 01:13:30,374
We must do something for him!

538
01:13:30,501 --> 01:13:32,571
Brothers, better save ourselves!

539
01:13:58,821 --> 01:14:01,733
Where did they take him?
Where have they taken him?!

540
01:14:01,861 --> 01:14:05,012
- He's the one who got the soldiers.
- Zerah...

541
01:14:05,901 --> 01:14:07,380
Zerah...

542
01:14:07,501 --> 01:14:09,059
Zerah.

543
01:14:09,861 --> 01:14:12,694
I must speak to Zerah.
I must speak to Zerah!

544
01:14:12,821 --> 01:14:15,210
Is he in here? Did they bring him here?

545
01:14:15,341 --> 01:14:16,854
Who?

546
01:14:16,981 --> 01:14:18,937
Jesus!

547
01:14:19,181 --> 01:14:21,137
Master Zerah, please,...

548
01:14:21,261 --> 01:14:23,252
..I don't understand this man.

549
01:14:23,381 --> 01:14:25,531
- Zerah... Zerah...
- Yes?

550
01:14:26,581 --> 01:14:30,290
Where is this meeting with Caiaphas?
I must be there with Jesus!

551
01:14:30,421 --> 01:14:31,649
Meeting?

552
01:14:31,781 --> 01:14:33,214
There's no meeting.

553
01:14:33,341 --> 01:14:34,694
What?

554
01:14:35,381 --> 01:14:37,337
There's a trial.

555
01:14:37,461 --> 01:14:40,021
Your Jesus is accused of blasphemy.

556
01:14:46,861 --> 01:14:50,058
You've been an invaluable
help to us, Judas.

557
01:14:50,181 --> 01:14:52,775
Come and see me when all this is over.

558
01:14:55,981 --> 01:14:56,936
Oh!

559
01:15:10,141 --> 01:15:12,609
Well, you got what you wanted.

560
01:15:13,661 --> 01:15:15,174
So get out of here.

561
01:15:15,301 --> 01:15:17,690
Come on, get out of here, move yourself!

562
01:15:22,021 --> 01:15:26,651
I've never understood how that liar
could have fooled so many people.

563
01:15:26,781 --> 01:15:28,931
You believed in him, didn't you?

564
01:15:29,061 --> 01:15:32,690
Well, l admit l believed in him,
but we all believed in him.

565
01:15:32,821 --> 01:15:36,450
- Now you know the truth!
- He said many things that l liked.

566
01:15:36,581 --> 01:15:38,537
And he did some good things.

567
01:15:38,661 --> 01:15:40,891
Good things?
They were tricks of the devil!

568
01:15:41,021 --> 01:15:45,219
All right! We know that he was a
liar and a blasphemer and he betrayed us.

569
01:15:45,341 --> 01:15:46,820
And now he will pay.

570
01:15:48,221 --> 01:15:51,531
I'm sorry to wake you up,
but they've arrested the Nazarene.

571
01:15:51,661 --> 01:15:55,097
- They did?
- Yes. In the garden of Gethsemane.

572
01:15:59,221 --> 01:16:00,574
Master Nicodemus...

573
01:16:21,901 --> 01:16:23,857
Brethren! Brethren!

574
01:16:25,221 --> 01:16:27,291
Brethren!

575
01:16:28,541 --> 01:16:32,580
Caiaphas, that he is bound like
a common thief! lt's most unseemly, sir.

576
01:16:35,541 --> 01:16:38,055
Jesus, it is not our intention...

577
01:16:39,101 --> 01:16:41,057
..to treat you as a criminal.

578
01:16:41,181 --> 01:16:42,739
But...

579
01:16:42,861 --> 01:16:46,695
..we want you to explain
to this assembly...

580
01:16:46,821 --> 01:16:48,777
..the nature of your teachings.

581
01:16:48,901 --> 01:16:52,576
What is this doctrine...

582
01:16:52,701 --> 01:16:56,137
..you and your disciples
are spreading through Judaea?

583
01:16:59,541 --> 01:17:01,497
l have spoken openly...

584
01:17:03,221 --> 01:17:05,177
..for all the world to hear.

585
01:17:06,821 --> 01:17:09,733
l have taught in the synagogues
and in the Temple.

586
01:17:09,861 --> 01:17:11,817
I have said nothing in secret.

587
01:17:12,661 --> 01:17:14,219
So...

588
01:17:15,421 --> 01:17:17,377
..why do you ask me?

589
01:17:20,381 --> 01:17:22,337
Ask those who heard me.

590
01:17:24,021 --> 01:17:26,489
They are my witnesses.

591
01:17:27,861 --> 01:17:28,850
Caiaphas,...

592
01:17:28,981 --> 01:17:30,539
..I have heard him preach.

593
01:17:30,661 --> 01:17:35,451
l find nothing in his doctrine which
denies the basic principles of our faith.

594
01:17:35,581 --> 01:17:39,574
Rabbi, we fail to understand
the meaning of many of your sayings.

595
01:17:39,701 --> 01:17:42,659
For instance,
there are witnesses who say that...

596
01:17:42,781 --> 01:17:45,932
..you claim that
you could destroy the Temple...

597
01:17:46,061 --> 01:17:49,656
..and rebuild it in three days!

598
01:17:49,781 --> 01:17:52,853
No-one could rebuild the Temple
in three days.

599
01:17:52,981 --> 01:17:56,132
What he's said must have
some symbolic meaning. Come...

600
01:17:56,261 --> 01:17:58,775
l heard him say
he could rebuild it in two days!

601
01:17:58,901 --> 01:18:01,859
Three days, four days, do you hear?

602
01:18:01,981 --> 01:18:05,735
- Witnesses can't even agree.
- How can we remember every detail?

603
01:18:05,861 --> 01:18:09,570
There was a riot,
which Jesus himself provoked,...

604
01:18:09,701 --> 01:18:12,738
..but for which the Romans
will hold us responsible!

605
01:18:12,861 --> 01:18:14,772
The riot was provoked by Barabbas!

606
01:18:14,901 --> 01:18:18,814
The Romans need no excuse!
We know what they have done to us!

607
01:18:18,941 --> 01:18:20,977
All of us here can remember...

608
01:18:22,021 --> 01:18:24,660
..the occasion, not so many years back,...

609
01:18:26,021 --> 01:18:31,573
..when over a thousand of our people
were nailed to the walls of Jerusalem...

610
01:18:31,661 --> 01:18:37,293
..because there weren't enough scaffolds
to satisfy the Romans' lust for blood!

611
01:18:37,381 --> 01:18:41,533
None of us, I'm sure,
wants to give any more victims...

612
01:18:41,661 --> 01:18:43,970
..to Pontius Pilate... than we can prevent.

613
01:18:44,101 --> 01:18:45,978
Of course not, Joseph.

614
01:18:46,101 --> 01:18:50,538
We're all agreed upon that.
As Caiaphas has said, this is not a trial.

615
01:18:50,661 --> 01:18:53,812
We... We left our homes,
we came here tonight,...

616
01:18:53,941 --> 01:18:58,935
..hoping that Jesus of Nazareth would
explain to us the purpose of his mission,...

617
01:18:59,061 --> 01:19:02,212
..and help to heal the divisions
in our community.

618
01:19:02,341 --> 01:19:07,017
Brother, we have often heard that you
have come to bring love and brotherhood.

619
01:19:07,141 --> 01:19:11,851
I beg you,
bring peace to our gathering tonight.

620
01:19:13,341 --> 01:19:15,297
Tell me,...

621
01:19:17,181 --> 01:19:20,332
..it has been said
that you proclaimed yourself...

622
01:19:21,741 --> 01:19:23,697
..the Son of God.

623
01:19:25,861 --> 01:19:27,817
I ask you now,...

624
01:19:27,941 --> 01:19:32,776
..in the name of the Eternal,...

625
01:19:35,301 --> 01:19:37,610
..are you...

626
01:19:37,741 --> 01:19:39,971
..the Messiah,...

627
01:19:40,101 --> 01:19:43,298
..the Son of God?

628
01:19:53,541 --> 01:19:54,656
I am.

629
01:19:55,941 --> 01:19:57,897
He must be mad!

630
01:20:12,301 --> 01:20:14,337
And you shall see the Son of Man...

631
01:20:15,581 --> 01:20:19,460
..sitting at the right hand
of the power of God.

632
01:20:19,581 --> 01:20:21,572
Hear, O lsrael,...

633
01:20:22,821 --> 01:20:25,130
..the Lord our God,...

634
01:20:26,381 --> 01:20:28,417
..the Lord is one!

635
01:20:41,701 --> 01:20:43,657
We have heard enough.

636
01:20:44,701 --> 01:20:47,852
Let him be taken before
the procurator, Pontius Pilate,...

637
01:20:49,621 --> 01:20:52,419
..in whose hands lies the final authority...

638
01:20:53,341 --> 01:20:55,297
..for trial and judgment.

639
01:21:19,061 --> 01:21:21,097
They got him at last!

640
01:21:21,221 --> 01:21:23,132
Let me get closer!

641
01:21:24,621 --> 01:21:26,976
They should crucify him!

642
01:21:27,101 --> 01:21:29,057
Son of God?!

643
01:21:29,861 --> 01:21:31,374
Kill him!

644
01:21:31,501 --> 01:21:33,219
Stone him!

645
01:21:33,341 --> 01:21:34,694
Blasphemer!

646
01:21:34,821 --> 01:21:36,777
Well, what happened to him?

647
01:21:38,061 --> 01:21:40,939
They're sending him to Pontius Pilate.

648
01:21:41,061 --> 01:21:43,336
We know how that will end up, don't we?

649
01:21:46,101 --> 01:21:48,695
Wait a minute! I know you.

650
01:21:48,821 --> 01:21:51,176
You were with that Jesus!

651
01:21:51,301 --> 01:21:54,179
- You're one of his followers.
- No, l don't know him.

652
01:21:54,301 --> 01:21:56,053
But he is. Look!

653
01:21:56,181 --> 01:21:59,218
And l know him.
He is one of his followers.

654
01:21:59,341 --> 01:22:02,777
- Yes! I've seen him! I've seen him!
- No!

655
01:22:02,901 --> 01:22:04,857
He's a liar! Arrest him!

656
01:22:05,581 --> 01:22:07,856
l tell you, l don't know him!

657
01:22:09,381 --> 01:22:10,609
Help me!

658
01:22:10,741 --> 01:22:12,333
What's going on?

659
01:22:12,461 --> 01:22:14,531
He's a friend of Jesus, a disciple.

660
01:22:14,661 --> 01:22:16,617
Don't let him go!

661
01:22:17,781 --> 01:22:19,737
Please...

662
01:22:20,781 --> 01:22:22,339
They're mistaken.

663
01:22:22,461 --> 01:22:25,100
I don't know this Jesus they speak of...

664
01:22:25,221 --> 01:22:27,212
..nor have I ever heard of him.

665
01:22:27,341 --> 01:22:30,378
Go! Just keep quiet here!

666
01:22:30,501 --> 01:22:32,890
Don't you know you're on sacred ground?

667
01:23:50,501 --> 01:23:51,980
Free Barabbas!

668
01:23:52,101 --> 01:23:53,659
Set Barabbas free!

669
01:23:54,501 --> 01:23:56,856
- Let Barabbas go!
- He's one of us!

670
01:23:56,981 --> 01:23:58,334
Free Barabbas!

671
01:23:58,461 --> 01:24:01,259
You had no right to arrest him!
Free Barabbas!

672
01:24:11,301 --> 01:24:13,257
- Welcome, Proc...
- Welcome?!

673
01:24:13,381 --> 01:24:17,932
I Ieave for one week and I come back to
a mob in the street, and you dare to say...

674
01:24:18,061 --> 01:24:20,017
.."welcome"!

675
01:24:21,981 --> 01:24:23,937
Who's this Barabbas?

676
01:24:24,941 --> 01:24:28,854
He's a Zealot we arrested.
His followers have disturbed the crowds.

677
01:24:28,981 --> 01:24:32,212
l don't think their noise
will disturb my judgment.

678
01:24:33,901 --> 01:24:35,414
Look,...

679
01:24:35,541 --> 01:24:38,009
..take a hundred men and clear the street.

680
01:24:38,141 --> 01:24:40,097
I'm tired.

681
01:24:40,581 --> 01:24:42,572
With respect,...

682
01:24:42,701 --> 01:24:45,010
- ..Procurator...
- Please, l'm so tired!

683
01:24:45,141 --> 01:24:47,860
Jerusalem is full of people.
There are many hotheads.

684
01:24:47,981 --> 01:24:52,497
Yes, and they'll cool when they see
the example we make of their Barabbas.

685
01:25:11,101 --> 01:25:13,661
Pontius Pilate,
l'm afraid there's another case.

686
01:25:13,781 --> 01:25:16,739
- Another one?
- Yes, submitted by the Sanhedrin itself.

687
01:25:16,861 --> 01:25:21,059
- lt concerns a Galilean preacher.
- I am not interested in their preachers...

688
01:25:21,181 --> 01:25:23,092
..or their prophets. You know that.

689
01:25:23,221 --> 01:25:25,177
Yes, of course, I know that.

690
01:25:25,701 --> 01:25:30,456
The Sanhedrin, whose co-operation
has been very useful to us,...

691
01:25:30,541 --> 01:25:33,613
..consider it extremely important.

692
01:25:35,581 --> 01:25:37,014
Even urgent.

693
01:25:37,141 --> 01:25:39,575
Urgent?! Urgent to whom?!

694
01:25:44,781 --> 01:25:46,339
I'm sorry.

695
01:25:47,101 --> 01:25:48,659
I'm sorry.

696
01:25:49,421 --> 01:25:51,377
Maybe next week.

697
01:25:52,981 --> 01:25:54,539
But first...

698
01:25:55,461 --> 01:25:57,417
..we'll deal with Barabbas.

699
01:25:58,781 --> 01:26:02,933
Pilate, there's a delegation
from the Sanhedrin waiting outside.

700
01:26:03,421 --> 01:26:05,491
lt is led by Zerah himself.

701
01:26:05,621 --> 01:26:09,500
They have this preacher,
this Jesus of Nazareth, with them.

702
01:26:09,621 --> 01:26:11,577
They want you to judge him.

703
01:26:11,701 --> 01:26:13,180
Judge him?

704
01:26:13,301 --> 01:26:16,418
Zerah himself? lt must be important.

705
01:26:16,501 --> 01:26:18,457
No. No, no, no.

706
01:26:18,541 --> 01:26:21,738
I don't want to get involved
in their religious quarrels.

707
01:26:21,861 --> 01:26:24,819
This is the monthly report of the province.

708
01:26:30,221 --> 01:26:34,214
lt's wise not to offend them unnecessarily.
I think you should see them.

709
01:26:35,421 --> 01:26:37,377
Well, have them brought in.

710
01:26:40,261 --> 01:26:42,172
Don't stand there. Bring them in.

711
01:26:42,301 --> 01:26:47,500
Pilate, I regret... l'm afraid
we must go out to them.

712
01:26:49,181 --> 01:26:50,580
We must go to them?

713
01:26:50,701 --> 01:26:52,657
Yes, according to their...

714
01:26:53,541 --> 01:26:55,099
..beliefs...

715
01:26:55,221 --> 01:26:57,974
Well, they cannot
come into a house of a Roman,...

716
01:26:58,101 --> 01:27:00,171
..not on Passover.

717
01:27:00,301 --> 01:27:02,257
They would be defiled.

718
01:27:07,621 --> 01:27:09,179
Defiled.

719
01:27:10,541 --> 01:27:12,497
I forgot about that.

720
01:27:14,221 --> 01:27:15,779
All right.

721
01:27:17,221 --> 01:27:19,177
We'll go to them.

722
01:27:20,301 --> 01:27:22,257
Bring them to the Great Hall.

723
01:27:28,301 --> 01:27:31,054
How does one govern such people?

724
01:27:44,301 --> 01:27:45,859
Procurator,...

725
01:27:46,541 --> 01:27:49,738
..we have found that this man,
Jesus of Nazareth,...

726
01:27:49,861 --> 01:27:54,810
..distorts our people's views on the
relationship between God and the state.

727
01:27:54,941 --> 01:27:59,412
Furthermore,
he perverts the very heart of our religion.

728
01:28:00,901 --> 01:28:03,461
l'm not concerned with
your religious laws.

729
01:28:03,581 --> 01:28:08,132
My function as governor here is to keep
the peace and administer Roman justice.

730
01:28:08,261 --> 01:28:14,177
We know that, Procurator, but this man
also threatens the established order.

731
01:28:14,301 --> 01:28:17,691
lf he were not a criminal,
we would not have brought him to you.

732
01:28:17,821 --> 01:28:22,133
He calls himself the Christ,
which means the Anointed One.

733
01:28:26,021 --> 01:28:27,739
Thank you.

734
01:28:27,861 --> 01:28:29,419
I too know some Greek.

735
01:28:31,101 --> 01:28:32,932
What else has he done?

736
01:28:33,061 --> 01:28:35,939
Has he spoken against the Emperor
or against Rome?

737
01:28:37,381 --> 01:28:41,340
Well, Procurator, not directly, no, but...

738
01:28:41,461 --> 01:28:46,171
Not directly? Then you'll have to
judge him according to your Law.

739
01:28:50,981 --> 01:28:54,860
Procurator, for us
this man Jesus is a blasphemer.

740
01:28:54,981 --> 01:28:59,930
lf we were a self-governing nation,
we'd have the right to exact punishment...

741
01:29:00,021 --> 01:29:02,012
..under the Law of Moses.

742
01:29:02,141 --> 01:29:05,577
He entered Jerusalem
calling himself the King of the Jews!

743
01:29:05,701 --> 01:29:07,657
A claim we totally reject!

744
01:29:09,181 --> 01:29:11,137
King of the Jews?

745
01:29:11,261 --> 01:29:16,176
Well, whatever else he may have done,
such a claim is treason.

746
01:29:18,021 --> 01:29:19,977
