..herbs and spices.

1014
01:59:50,821 --> 01:59:52,812
It is our custom.

1015
01:59:57,221 --> 02:00:00,179
Why didn't you do that
when you brought him here?

1016
02:00:00,301 --> 02:00:02,861
The Sabbath began.
We could not buy them.

1017
02:00:03,581 --> 02:00:05,458
What do you think?

1018
02:00:05,581 --> 02:00:08,095
They're only three women. Let them go.

1019
02:00:08,221 --> 02:00:12,294
l suppose it'll be all right.
You'll need an army to move that stone.

1020
02:00:12,421 --> 02:00:16,175
All right, then. Let's go together,
but we'll need some help.

1021
02:00:16,781 --> 02:00:18,851
Hey, Lentulus, wake up!

1022
02:00:18,981 --> 02:00:20,733
Come with us!

1023
02:00:20,861 --> 02:00:22,817
Marcus, you watch the bridge!

1024
02:00:24,061 --> 02:00:26,939
All those priests, too.
Are they still around?

1025
02:00:31,981 --> 02:00:35,132
Can't wait to get away from this place,
back to Rome.

1026
02:00:42,461 --> 02:00:44,417
Where are you going?

1027
02:00:48,141 --> 02:00:50,609
Why do you seek the living
among the dead?

1028
02:00:53,981 --> 02:00:55,937
Jesus is not there.

1029
02:01:08,781 --> 02:01:10,737
He's gone!

1030
02:01:13,021 --> 02:01:14,977
Come!

1031
02:01:23,221 --> 02:01:25,177
Jesus is not here.

1032
02:01:37,021 --> 02:01:40,331
- Are you sure?
- I swear by Jupiter, HercuIes and Mars!

1033
02:01:40,461 --> 02:01:42,736
You've been awake all night
and haven't moved.

1034
02:01:42,861 --> 02:01:46,740
That's right! We were given strict orders.
Nobody's been near that tomb.

1035
02:01:46,861 --> 02:01:49,500
Those Jewish priests
were with us all the time.

1036
02:01:49,621 --> 02:01:51,896
Well, then, who moved the stone?

1037
02:01:56,701 --> 02:01:59,454
- Who is it?
- Me. Philip.

1038
02:02:02,421 --> 02:02:04,377
- Did anyone follow you?
- No.

1039
02:02:06,221 --> 02:02:08,781
- Are you sure?
- Of course l'm sure.

1040
02:02:11,341 --> 02:02:13,297
Are they still looking for us?

1041
02:02:13,421 --> 02:02:17,096
On every corner one sees
Temple guards and Roman soldiers.

1042
02:02:17,421 --> 02:02:20,413
This place isn't safe.
We must go somewhere else.

1043
02:02:20,541 --> 02:02:24,011
- But where can we go?
- I wish we could go to Galilee.

1044
02:02:25,901 --> 02:02:27,573
Peter...

1045
02:02:27,701 --> 02:02:29,657
Peter!

1046
02:02:30,861 --> 02:02:32,579
Tell us,...

1047
02:02:32,701 --> 02:02:34,134
..what should we do?

1048
02:02:34,261 --> 02:02:36,980
We must do what the Master
would have wanted.

1049
02:02:38,701 --> 02:02:40,817
The Master's dead, Peter.

1050
02:02:46,181 --> 02:02:49,139
- I thought you said you weren't followed!
- I wasn't!

1051
02:02:56,901 --> 02:02:58,857
- Mary...
- Peter!

1052
02:03:01,501 --> 02:03:03,457
All of you,...

1053
02:03:04,301 --> 02:03:06,257
..I have seen him.

1054
02:03:06,381 --> 02:03:08,337
Seen who?

1055
02:03:09,501 --> 02:03:10,729
The Master.

1056
02:03:12,021 --> 02:03:13,739
You've seen him?

1057
02:03:13,861 --> 02:03:15,135
Yes.

1058
02:03:17,261 --> 02:03:18,819
He is risen.

1059
02:03:26,821 --> 02:03:27,970
I saw him.

1060
02:03:28,101 --> 02:03:29,659
I saw him!

1061
02:03:29,781 --> 02:03:33,615
This morning we went to the tomb,
and near the tomb was a man...

1062
02:03:34,501 --> 02:03:36,457
..and a young boy.

1063
02:03:36,981 --> 02:03:41,179
And the man said to me, "Why do you
look for the living among the dead?"

1064
02:03:43,181 --> 02:03:45,137
"Jesus is not here."

1065
02:03:45,861 --> 02:03:49,251
So we went to the tomb
and we saw the stone was upturned.

1066
02:03:50,261 --> 02:03:53,571
The grave... the tomb was open.

1067
02:03:57,101 --> 02:03:59,490
We looked for him.

1068
02:03:59,621 --> 02:04:01,577
He was not there.

1069
02:04:08,501 --> 02:04:12,414
- You mean his body wasn't there?
- Has it been stolen?

1070
02:04:12,541 --> 02:04:14,896
No, no, no. Let me finish.

1071
02:04:16,301 --> 02:04:18,531
When we were leaving the cemetery,...

1072
02:04:18,661 --> 02:04:20,617
..I saw another man.

1073
02:04:21,261 --> 02:04:23,217
He saw how distraught we were.

1074
02:04:25,141 --> 02:04:27,097
He said, "Woman,...

1075
02:04:29,461 --> 02:04:31,417
..why do you weep?"

1076
02:04:33,421 --> 02:04:35,377
And then he said my name.

1077
02:04:36,661 --> 02:04:38,617
"Mary..."

1078
02:04:40,181 --> 02:04:42,137
"Mary."

1079
02:04:43,461 --> 02:04:46,021
And it was then that I saw...

1080
02:04:46,221 --> 02:04:48,177
..it was Jesus.

1081
02:04:50,421 --> 02:04:52,377
l fell to my knees...

1082
02:04:52,501 --> 02:04:54,856
..and I reached for him.

1083
02:04:55,381 --> 02:04:57,337
"Touch me not,...

1084
02:04:58,261 --> 02:05:01,412
..for I have not yet
ascended to my Father", he said.

1085
02:05:03,301 --> 02:05:05,257
"But go to my brothers,...

1086
02:05:05,381 --> 02:05:07,372
..and tell them."

1087
02:05:20,221 --> 02:05:22,177
You don't believe me.

1088
02:05:23,861 --> 02:05:25,817
You don't believe me!

1089
02:05:31,701 --> 02:05:33,657
l tell you, l saw him!

1090
02:05:33,781 --> 02:05:35,737
- It was our Lord!
- Mary...

1091
02:05:35,861 --> 02:05:37,658
Mary!

1092
02:05:37,781 --> 02:05:39,737
John...

1093
02:05:39,941 --> 02:05:41,340
Oh, John...

1094
02:05:42,381 --> 02:05:44,337
You don't believe me.

1095
02:05:44,461 --> 02:05:46,019
You!

1096
02:05:46,861 --> 02:05:48,533
Mary...

1097
02:05:48,661 --> 02:05:50,617
You're tired.

1098
02:05:51,501 --> 02:05:53,059
Please!

1099
02:05:54,421 --> 02:05:56,377
Please go.

1100
02:05:57,261 --> 02:05:59,217
I saw him, John.

1101
02:05:59,341 --> 02:06:01,297
I saw him.

1102
02:06:03,821 --> 02:06:05,777
Women's fantasies.

1103
02:06:07,221 --> 02:06:08,779
Fantasies?

1104
02:06:09,781 --> 02:06:11,737
Was his death a fantasy?!

1105
02:06:12,221 --> 02:06:14,177
I saw him die!

1106
02:06:14,301 --> 02:06:16,257
I was there and I wept at his feet!

1107
02:06:17,181 --> 02:06:19,741
Why should he not then appear to me?!

1108
02:06:21,061 --> 02:06:23,017
He is risen.

1109
02:06:32,461 --> 02:06:34,417
He told me to tell you,...

1110
02:06:36,941 --> 02:06:38,897
..and I have done so.

1111
02:06:50,541 --> 02:06:55,695
You wouldn't believe her! When he raised
Jairus's daughter, you didn't believe it!

1112
02:06:55,821 --> 02:06:58,779
What do you mean?
You believe her story?!

1113
02:07:03,341 --> 02:07:05,297
Well, do any of you believe it?

1114
02:07:06,141 --> 02:07:08,450
Do you, Andrew?

1115
02:07:08,581 --> 02:07:10,537
Do you, James?

1116
02:07:12,141 --> 02:07:14,097
And you, Matthew?!

1117
02:07:23,141 --> 02:07:24,699
Do you,...

1118
02:07:25,741 --> 02:07:27,299
..Peter?

1119
02:07:31,901 --> 02:07:33,459
Yes.

1120
02:07:35,301 --> 02:07:36,859
How can you?

1121
02:07:38,741 --> 02:07:40,697
Because he said so.

1122
02:07:43,181 --> 02:07:45,137
Because he wanted it to be so.

1123
02:07:48,621 --> 02:07:50,737
He wanted everything to happen...

1124
02:07:53,141 --> 02:07:55,097
..just as it did.

1125
02:07:59,061 --> 02:08:01,017
And I have always believed him.

1126
02:08:01,141 --> 02:08:03,211
But... Peter,...

1127
02:08:03,341 --> 02:08:06,651
..you denied him.
You denied him three times!

1128
02:08:06,781 --> 02:08:08,339
Yes!

1129
02:08:09,581 --> 02:08:12,095
I denied him because I was a coward!

1130
02:08:14,821 --> 02:08:16,777
We are all cowards!

1131
02:08:18,581 --> 02:08:22,256
We accused Judas of being a traitor,
but we all betrayed him!

1132
02:08:24,341 --> 02:08:26,013
We all...

1133
02:08:26,141 --> 02:08:27,893
..abandoned him.

1134
02:08:28,021 --> 02:08:33,414
At least our brothers in the Sanhedrin
who condemned him didn't know him!

1135
02:08:33,541 --> 02:08:35,497
The Romans...

1136
02:08:37,741 --> 02:08:39,697
..did not know him.

1137
02:08:39,821 --> 02:08:41,777
But we...

1138
02:08:43,301 --> 02:08:45,257
We ate with him.

1139
02:08:47,221 --> 02:08:49,177
We lived with him.

1140
02:08:51,341 --> 02:08:53,297
We knew he was the Christ!

1141
02:08:54,421 --> 02:08:56,377
And still we betrayed him!

1142
02:08:59,541 --> 02:09:01,896
Brothers, don't you... can't you see?

1143
02:09:05,461 --> 02:09:07,417
Thomas...

1144
02:09:12,701 --> 02:09:14,896
You asked me if I believe he is risen.

1145
02:09:17,061 --> 02:09:19,017
Yes, I do.

1146
02:09:20,221 --> 02:09:22,735
For l know in my heart he will not...

1147
02:09:23,741 --> 02:09:25,697
..abandon us.

1148
02:09:27,781 --> 02:09:30,170
I know in my heart he has forgiven me...

1149
02:09:36,221 --> 02:09:38,291
Us.

1150
02:09:53,061 --> 02:09:55,017
Forgiven all of us.

1151
02:10:08,981 --> 02:10:10,937
This is precisely what I feared.

1152
02:10:11,061 --> 02:10:14,610
His disciples must have removed
the stone and taken away the body.

1153
02:10:14,741 --> 02:10:17,619
lmpossible!
I had guards here as you requested.

1154
02:10:17,741 --> 02:10:20,050
And your priests were here, too.

1155
02:10:38,141 --> 02:10:40,416
Now it begins.

1156
02:10:49,821 --> 02:10:51,777
lt all begins.

1157
02:11:03,301 --> 02:11:05,257
lt was written...

1158
02:11:07,221 --> 02:11:09,177
..the Son ofMan will suffer,...

1159
02:11:11,421 --> 02:11:13,377
..and on the third day...

1160
02:11:13,981 --> 02:11:16,859
..will rise again from the dead
to enter his glory.

1161
02:11:19,621 --> 02:11:21,657
You are my witnesses to this.

1162
02:11:25,821 --> 02:11:28,893
Now my Father in heaven
is reconciled to the world.

1163
02:11:31,621 --> 02:11:33,577
And as he sent me...

1164
02:11:35,621 --> 02:11:37,577
..so I am sending you.

1165
02:11:48,181 --> 02:11:50,137
Receive the Holy Spirit.

1166
02:11:53,421 --> 02:11:55,981
Go like lambs among wolves.

1167
02:12:00,501 --> 02:12:03,857
Make disciples of all nations.

1168
02:12:06,381 --> 02:12:09,134
Baptise them in the name of the Father,...

1169
02:12:09,261 --> 02:12:11,217
..and of the Son,...

1170
02:12:11,341 --> 02:12:13,616
..and of the Holy Ghost.

1171
02:12:13,741 --> 02:12:17,256
Teach them the gospel
and the commandments l gave you.

1172
02:12:19,501 --> 02:12:21,093
Now...

1173
02:12:21,221 --> 02:12:24,293
..I am leaving the world again,...

1174
02:12:24,421 --> 02:12:27,572
..and going to the Father.

1175
02:12:32,701 --> 02:12:34,657
Oh, Lord, stay with us.

1176
02:12:37,181 --> 02:12:39,137
The night is falling.

1177
02:12:40,821 --> 02:12:42,777
The day is almost over.

1178
02:12:48,341 --> 02:12:50,297
Don't be afraid.

1179
02:12:52,421 --> 02:12:54,377
I am with you every day...

1180
02:12:56,301 --> 02:12:58,257
..till the end of time.

1181
02:14:58,181 --> 02:15:00,900
Visiontext subtitles:
Natasha Cohn & Helen Stewart

